photo eyes or sensors Safe-T-Beam are an important safety device and they need to work properly.";i:10;s:151:"The requirement for these safety devices was to reduce the number of deaths to children who become entrapped under garage doors with automatic openers.";i:11;s:120:"On rare occasions the angle at which the sun shines onto one of the garage door sensors causes the circuit to be broken.";i:12;s:96:"Having a sun shield installed on the sensor by a garage door specialist may resolve the problem.";i:13;s:36:"Contact Safe Way Garage Doors Today.";i:14;s:55:"Safe Way Garage Doors Inc is owner-operated since 1998.";i:15;s:159:"If one of your sensors has a light active and the other is either dark or blinking then you can be sure that the problem lies with the dark or blinking sensor.";i:16;s:115:"The photo-eyes should be held in small mounting brackets or frames and you can manually adjust them with your hand.";i:17;s:88:"You could swap the emitter and detector units so that the emitter is on the sunlit side.";i:18;s:61:"It doesnt matter if the emitter is being blasted by sunlight.";i:19;s:40:"Only the detector needs to be protected.";i:20;s:129:"Of course you might just be changing the time of day of your problem if the other side of the door is sunlit at a different time.";i:21;s:65:"How can I bypass the photo electric eye on my garage door opener.";i:22;s:79:"It is the sun light coming into the garage - Answered by a verified Technician.";i:23;s:107:"If sunlight shines on the garage door sensor the infrared light wont run between the two photo eye sensors.";i:24;s:82:"The sensors cannot signal to one another to close the garage so it will stay open.";i:25;s:56:"Three Ways to Block the Sun from Shining on the Sensors.";i:26;s:115:"If you notice that your garage door struggles to close on sunny days the sunlight is probably blinding the sensors.";i:27;s:161:"If you only have a problem closing your garage door at certain times of the day the sun MIGHT BE shining int